				<td colspan="2"><span>Not sure that you read the recent change to the nerf, Ruser, sorry about this if you did. :p
<br />

<br />
But you don't have to stand still to AE DoT anymore (I guess that was the old way they nerfed it?), and the really good news is that even if the mobs are moving, the Slow and/or whatever other debuff you were using stays on them (they just don't take the damage)....  But the mobs have to more or less stand still, now.  
<br />
And in all of the places I use AE DoTs (tier 5 of Time, zerging easy LDoNs, and pharming greens), they do.  More or less, as he described in his post.  Pushing them with melee/stuns shouldn't block the DoT damage.
<br />

<br />
What's wrong with AE Kiting 10 golems?  Aside from the fact that it apparently creates server lag (according to his posts), hogs a lot of content that full groups could be enjoying (not an issue in most of the dead zones Bards usually AE in, granted), and that it makes every other class in the game green with envy (just the thought of soloing meelions of mobs at once, never mind other classes raking in similar exp by other means)...  Not much.
<br />
Now, if somebody is using a macro program to AFK exp...  I think most would agree that that's a problem.  And I'd bet dollars to pesos that the macros are the real reason they are cracking down on this.  Oh, and the reason you don't see zones packed with AEing Bards is most zones you can AE in can only support ONE such Bard.
<br />

<br />
---
<br />

<br />
As for the songs, ya most of them are cookie-cutter boring upgrades.  More Mezzes, more Chants, more Haste songs, more Manasongs.  Wheeeee?  Standard set of upgrades.
<br />

<br />
But then there's this gem:
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5374&amp;source=Test">http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5374&amp;source=Test</a>
<br />

<br />
And the new Charm looks promising (currently capped at level 68 mobs):
<br />
