				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Changes made to AE nerf<a name="60995"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 12:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It is a nerf -- no question.  In the minds of the devs, it was necessary to stop ae kiting.  Let's not argue whether they are right or not -- assume you're not changing their minds on that one.
<br />

<br />
Given that, consider what happened here -- they came up with an answer that most definitely whacked AE kiting.  We vehemently expressed our thought that this was NOT the right answer.  We urged them to find a way to re-code mobs so that mob reaction determined the affect of AE DoTs and not our actions -- and that is EXACTLY what they did.  Give Sony some credit for that much.  They really did a good job of trying to respond to our concerns.
<br />

<br />
I still think this nerfs more than AE kiting because if I adjust my own position relative to server tick timing, I will lose the benefit of the DoT damage as mobs react to my movement, but it is better than the first solution, I grant that.  For those worrying about push, note that Grumbuk said that if the code detects the mob TRYING to move, damage is not applied.  So presumably, that will not include push or knockback directly, though mobs reacting to push or knockback may negate damage.
<br />

<br />
Overall, give them an A for trying to accomodate our concerns.</span></td>
