				<td colspan="2"><span>There is surely some fine tuning that will need to be done. It bothers me a little that seemingly even a rooted mob that &quot;wants&quot; to move would not be affected.. and I don't think we should yet be comfortable that push won't be a problem. What happens, after all, when a mob is pushed? it very quickly tries to readjust the situation -- either by summoning (if available) or by moving. When I think about how frequently mobs that seem to be at melee range summon tanks into/past them to adjust the positioning, I wouldn't be surprised if even a mob being meleed avoids a lot of ticks simply due to repositioning issues. Even using the songs for an initial aggro boost would be difficult, as the range is small enough that by the time you can get close enough for the song to land, the mob will aggro and run towards you
<br />

<br />
While I respect that they are trying to accomodate our concerns and still deal with the AE issue, I truly don't foresee these songs being much use at all (with respect to their damage components) if this stays as it is currently being described. I'd prefer to have the songs replaced with something else that might actually stand a chance of being memmed. I think a limit to the number of targets affected would have been reasonable, but apparently something similar to the quad-kite restriction isn't deemed worth the coding time.
<br />

<br />
Of course, charm-kiting is another option we have (limited by mana regen, especially for those without top-end gear), but I am worried that this too will be nerfed as they try to prevent swarm-kiting (which has almost all of the same negatives from their perspective as AE kiting does). If our charm spells become melee-range only or non-moving only....</span></td>
